      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16/6/65 ¶  ¶ This day, dear Mr Gunn, I received your very kind letter of the 14th ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ together with the 4 Thylacine in excellent health. It is indeed a precious gift and I trust t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.06.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ronald Gunn</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A251 Gunn papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16/6/65</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Mr Gunn, I received your very kind letter of the 14th<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>together with the 4 Thylacine in excellent health. It is indeed a precious gift and I trust to fulfil now the wish of the Parisian Savants, who were so eager to secure this rare creature for the jardin des plantes. I shall not fail to render known who is the real donor.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The weather is now too cold to send the animals around Cape Horn. I shall probably wait til spring when the Yorkshire goes &amp; when I can place them together with the sheep on board under care of a very trustworthy man.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The fate of the animals is not known. There is no record of them having reached Paris<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>alive<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(donation lists,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bulletin de la Société impériale zoologique d'acclimatation</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>series 2, vol. 2 (1865), pp. 751-3, or<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>series 2, vol. 3<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1866), pp. 699-701). If they had died before the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Yorkshire</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>sailed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 15 November 1865 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 16 November, 1865, p. 4) specimens would probably have been deposited at the Museum in Melbourne or sent by Mueller to one or more European museums (see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Lucas<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(2013)), but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>International Thylacine Specimen Database has no record of any of the four animals (Stephen Sleightolme, Project Director,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>e-mail, 28 March 2024).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>If they had died on board, the remains would probably have been disposed of at sea.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>They are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>not mentioned<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in Paddle (2000), Holmes &amp; Linnard (2023) or Ashby (2022).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>As these animals most probably would breed in not too confined a state, the species, ere long perhaps extinct, might be kept up in menageries from your importation.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Paddle (1996).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray inform me, whether there is anything in my garden that I can send you? I am not certain that you have my last publication either, for instance lithograms of Victorian plants<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B65.02.06.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and also vol. IV fragmenta,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B65.02.09.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>perhaps neither the little books on the mosses and Chatham plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B64.10.03, B64.13.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— It will need merely a few lines to the Chief Secretary &amp; they will be supplied. Bentham goes rapidly on with the Australian General flora.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Myrtaceae, the main occupants of the 3 vol. will soon be done and I prepare now my material for the use of the 4th vol., especially to be devoted to Compositae &amp; to be elaborated in 1866. I should have done more, had not the anxieties for the Leichhardt search absorbed my spare time since the end of last year</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Is your poor friend quite recovered from his accident?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>James<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Grant. See M to R. Gunn, 20 May 1865.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have some very curious plants from Rockingham's Bay introduced into the 5th vol. of the fragmenta.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mostly collected by John Dallacy. The third fascicle of the volume, B65.07.03, was probably in press at the time of this letter.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Compositae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myrtaceae</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
